'''帕里斯丁王国'''，是[[赫梯帝国|赫梯帝国]]崩溃后主要的继承国之一<ref name="bryce">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=k0dbRu1TOgUC&pg=PA128#v=onepage&q&f=false|title= The World of The Neo-Hittite Kingdoms: A Political and Military History|author=Trevor Bryce|page= 128}}</ref>。其位置在今天的[[叙利亚|叙利亚]]西北部和[[土耳其|土耳其]]东南部。

== 历史 ==
[[File:NeoHittiteStates.gif|thumb]]
前12世纪，一度控制整个[[安纳托利亚|安纳托利亚]]和叙利亚西北部的赫梯帝国由于尚不明确的原因突然崩溃。随后，这一地区建立了大量新赫梯王国和城邦。帕里斯丁是其中位于今天土耳其东南部和叙利亚西北部的一个国家，其领土覆盖了西至[[安条克|安条克]]，东至[[阿勒颇|阿勒颇]]，南至[[哈马|哈马]]的广阔区域<ref name="bryce3">{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=q8Z7AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA111#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= Ancient Syria: A Three Thousand Year History |author= Trevor Bryce |page= 111 |access-date= 2016-11-22 |archive-date= 2015-10-16 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151016214636/https://books.google.com/books?id=q8Z7AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA111#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url= no }}</ref>。前10世纪，帕里斯丁被分为[[哈马|哈马]]、{{le|比特阿古西|Bit Agusi}}、{{le|帕丁|Pattin}}等几个国家<ref name="Singer">''Before and After the Storm: Crisis Years in Anatolia and Syria between the Fall of the Hittite Empire and the Beginning of a New Era (ca. 1220-1000 BC)'', A Symposium in Memory of Itamar Singer, University of Pavia, 2012 [http://www.academia.edu/5403302/The_Philistines_in_the_North_and_the_Kingdom_of_Taita_unpublished_paper_by_Itamar_Singer_zl_  p. 7+8] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140328061855/http://www.academia.edu/5403302/The_Philistines_in_the_North_and_the_Kingdom_of_Taita_unpublished_paper_by_Itamar_Singer_zl_ |date=2014-03-28 }}</ref>。

== 考古 ==
目前对于帕里斯丁的了解主要来源于国王泰塔及其王后<ref name="bryce"/>。土耳其[[哈塔伊省|哈塔伊省]]的{{le|特尔·塔伊纳特|Tell Tayinat}}考古遗址被认为是帕里斯丁的首都基那卢亚所在地。在那里发现过两个定居点，一个是[[爱琴海文明|爱琴海文明]]的渔业定居点，另一个是在其上方的铁器时代叙利亚－赫梯城市。后者即被认为是当时的首都遗址<ref name="bryce2">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=k0dbRu1TOgUC&pg=PA129#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= The World of The Neo-Hittite Kingdoms: A Political and Military History |author=Trevor Bryce|page= 129}}</ref>，出土文物中发现了Walistin的拼写<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zqQofdcZAGoC&pg=PA802#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= A Companion to the Archaeology of the Ancient Near East |author= D. T. Potts |page= 802}}</ref>。

在叙利亚{{le|Shaizar}}出土的一块石碑上也发现了帕里斯丁的名字。碑文显示，这是国王泰塔的王后库帕皮亚的纪念碑<ref name="Luw">{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=Tb4mzSQ2nJoC&pg=PA47#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= Iron Age Hieroglyphic Luwian Inscriptions |author=Annick Payne |page= 47}}</ref>。另外在{{le|Meharde}}发现了一块与国王泰塔相关的石碑，也显示了与帕里斯丁的关联<ref name="Luw"/>。在2003年，一座带有[[卢维语|卢维语]]题字的泰塔王雕像在[[阿勒颇城堡|阿勒颇城堡]]内出土，进一步证实了帕里斯丁的范围和影响<ref name="bryce" /><ref>{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=YMxY_hfXkCQC&pg=PA130#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= A New Luwian Stele and the Cult of the Storm-god at Til Barsib-Masuwari |author= Guy Bunnens |page= 130 |access-date= 2016-11-22 |archive-date= 2015-10-16 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151016214636/https://books.google.com/books?id=YMxY_hfXkCQC&pg=PA130#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

== 与非利士的联系 ==
[[File:Iron_Age_Temple_(photo_credit_Stephen_Batiuk).jpg|thumb]]
经语言学家解读，出土文物中的国名很有可能读作Palistin<ref name="bryce2" /> 。这一名称与“[[非利士|非利士]]”（[[埃及语|埃及语]]：Peleset，[[希伯来语|希伯来语]]：P'lishtim）的相似性使得一些考古学家认为帕里斯丁与日后的非利士人间存在紧密的联系<ref name="Ann">{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=gBCl2IQfNioC&pg=PA662#v=onepage&q&f=false |title= The Philistines and Other "Sea Peoples" in Text and Archaeology |author= Ann E. Killebrew |page= 662 |access-date= 2016-11-22 |archive-date= 2019-05-20 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190520075325/https://books.google.com/books?id=gBCl2IQfNioC&pg=PA662#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>Benjamin Sass, ''Taita, King of Palistin: Ca 950-900 BCE?'', University of Tel Aviv, 2010.</ref>，甚至是其起源地之一 <ref>[http://www.haaretz.com/jewish/archaeology/1.676943 Julia Fridman, 2015, "Riddle of the Ages Solved: Where Did the Philistines Come From?"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.haaretz.com/jewish/archaeology/1.676943 |date=20200522093341 }}, ''[[Haaretz|Haaretz]]'' (10 February 2016).</ref>
。然而，这一观点存在争议。叙利亚其他考古遗址中出土的文字显示了Wadasatini / Padasatini的拼写，以及Walistin的拼写也同时存在，且无法证明两个字母之间可以混用<ref name="bryce3" /><ref name="Ann" />。其他差异包括帕里斯丁遗址中出土的赫梯式陶器与爱琴海文明的陶器式样截然不同，以及帕里斯丁国王的赫梯式名字<ref name="Singer" />。

目前流行的假说认为，曾有一批来自爱琴海地区的定居者迁移至基那卢亚，虽然最后被当地居民同化，但却为此地留下了爱琴海文明式的名字，这一地名后来又影响了迁移至此的非利士人<ref name="Singer" /><ref name="Emanuel">Emanuel, Jeffrey P. "King Taita and His Palistin: Philstine State or Neo-Hittite Kingdom?" ''Antiguo Oriente'' 13 (2015), 11-40 [https://www.academia.edu/26654209/King_Taita_and_His_Palistin_Philistine_State_or_Neo-Hittite_Kingdom] {{Wayback|url=https://www.academia.edu/26654209/King_Taita_and_His_Palistin_Philistine_State_or_Neo-Hittite_Kingdom |date=20181210124449 }}</ref>。

